-- IFC Approves $30 Million Loan to Garanti’s Romanian Unit
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2012-02-23T10:59:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-23/ifc-approves-30-million-loan-to-garanti-s-romanian-unit.html
The  International Finance
Corporation , the  World Bank ’s investment arm, approved a 22.5
million-euro ($30 million) loan to the Romanian unit of Turkiye
Garanti Bankasi AS to finance small- and medium-sized business
managed by women, the IFC said in a statement today.  Turkiye Garanti Bankasi is  Turkey ’s biggest listed bank by
market value.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
